\begin{critbox}
\textbf{Six-Mark Execution: The Fetch Phase}\\
You must be able to list the exact register transfer sequence for the fetch phase:
\begin{enumerate}
    \item The PC contains the address of the next instruction.
    \item This address is copied from the PC to the MAR.
    \item The instruction at that address in memory is fetched along the data bus to the MDR.
    \item The PC is incremented by 1.
    \item The instruction in the MDR is copied to the CIR to be decoded.
\end{enumerate}
\end{critbox}

