\section{Homework Assignment}

\noindent\textbf{Question 4: Comprehensive System Analysis (14 Marks)}\\
A modern self-driving car relies heavily on an onboard computer system with a primary CPU, various memory modules, and multiple system buses. The system must process massive amounts of camera data in real-time to avoid collisions.
\begin{enumerate}[leftmargin=*, label=(\alph*)]
    \item The car's CPU uses the Program Counter (PC) and Current Instruction Register (CIR). Compare the roles of these two registers during the FDE cycle. \textit{[4 marks]}
    \item The system detects an unexpected pedestrian and the processor receives an immediate hardware interrupt. Explain what an interrupt is, and detail the steps the CPU takes to process it before returning to its original task. \textit{[6 marks]}
    \item A mechanic plugs a diagnostic tool into the car using a USB connection. State TWO advantages of using a Universal Serial Bus (USB) interface for this diagnostic tool. \textit{[4 marks]}
\end{enumerate}

